        "name": "brightics.function.evaluation$evaluate_classification",
        "context": "python",
        "label": "Evaluate Classification",
        "description": "This function computes the weighted F1 score, the accuracy, the precision, the recall.\nSuppose there are 1,2,...,n classes. Suppose that A(n) is the number of elements class n of a label and B(n) is the number of elements of class n of a prediction. Suppose further that A(n)=B(n) represents the number of elements of class n of both a label and a prediction.\nWe define 'recall by n' is (A(n)=B(n))/A(n) and 'precision by n' is (A(n)=B(n))/B(n) and 'f1 by n' is 2*('recall by n' * 'precision by n')/('recall by n' + 'precision by n').\nWeighted recall/precision/f1 is defined as (ratio of class 1 of a label) * (recall/precision/f1 by 1) + ... + (ratio of class n of a label) * (recall/precision/f1 by n).\nAccuracy is a sum of a ratio of true positive and true negative.",
